        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 5:02PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM CDT, NWS meteorologists were tracking strong thunderstorms
near Papineau, Beaverville, and Pittwood, and all were moving east
at around 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and localized tree damage.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Papineau, St. Anne, Martinton, Donovan, Mount Ayr, Brook, Goodland,
Foresman, Morocco, Sheldon, Iroquois, Beaverville, Kentland, Watseka,
and Hopkins Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
